      • test_delete_insert_00

        public void test_delete_insert_00()
                           throws org.openrdf.query.MalformedQueryException,
                                  TokenMgrError,
                                  ParseException
        DELETE/INSERT w/o WITH. 
         PREFIX foaf:  
 
 DELETE { ?person foaf:givenName 'Bill' }
 INSERT { ?person foaf:givenName 'William' }
 WHERE {
   ?person foaf:givenName 'Bill' .
   GRAPH  {
     ?person foaf:givenName 'Bill'
     }
 }
        Note: Since WITH is not given, the context position is null and the StatementPattern.Scope is StatementPattern.Scope.DEFAULT_CONTEXTS for any StatementPatternNode which is outside of a GRAPH group. Within a GRAPH group, the context is, of course, the constant IRI or variable specified by the GRAPH group and the StatementPattern.Scope is StatementPattern.Scope.NAMED_CONTEXTS.
        Throws:
        org.openrdf.query.MalformedQueryException
        TokenMgrError
        ParseException
        See Also:
        StatementPatternNode

      • test_delete_insert_01

        public void test_delete_insert_01()
                           throws org.openrdf.query.MalformedQueryException,
                                  TokenMgrError,
                                  ParseException
        DELETE/INSERT plus WITH to specify the graph. 
         PREFIX foaf:  
 
 WITH 
 DELETE { ?person foaf:givenName 'Bill' }
 INSERT { ?person foaf:givenName 'William' }
 WHERE {
   ?person foaf:givenName 'Bill' .
   GRAPH  {
     ?person foaf:givenName 'Bill'
     }
 }
        Note: The context position on the StatementPatternNode outside of the GRAPH group is bound to the constant specified by the WITH clause. WITH uri is a syntactic sugar for GRAPH uri {...}, so the StatementPatternNode is also marked as StatementPattern.Scope.NAMED_CONTEXTS.
        Throws:
        org.openrdf.query.MalformedQueryException
        TokenMgrError
        ParseException

                                  TokenMgrError,
                                  ParseException
        DELETE/INSERT and USING. 
         PREFIX foaf:  
 
 DELETE { ?person foaf:givenName 'Bill' }
 INSERT { ?person foaf:givenName 'William' }
 USING 
 WHERE {
   ?person foaf:givenName 'Bill' .
   GRAPH  {
     ?person foaf:givenName 'Bill'
     }
 }
        Note: WITH is not used, so there is no implicit GRAPH wrapping the INSERT clause, DELETE clause, and WHERE clause. Therefore, the context will be null for the statement patterns in the DELETE clause and INSERT clause and outside of the GRAPH clause in the WHERE clause.

                                            ParseException
        DELETE/INSERT with blank node in the DELETE template.

        Note: blank nodes are not allowed in the DELETE clause template (nor in DELETE DATA). This is because the blank nodes in the DELETE clause are distinct for each solution plugged into that template. Thus they can not match anything in the database.
